OTHER CONTINGENCIES

THE CORPORATION AND CERTAIN OF ITS CONSOLIDATED SUBSIDIARIES WERE CONTINGENTLY LIABLE AT DECEMBER 31, 2008, FOR $7,847 MILLION, PRIMARILY RELATING TO GUARANTEES FOR NOTES, LOANS AND PERFORMANCE UNDER CONTRACTS. INCLUDED IN THIS AMOUNT

WERE GUARANTEES BY CONSOLIDATED AFFILIATES OF $6,102 MILLION, REPRESENTING EXXONMOBILS SHARE OF OBLIGATIONS OF CERTAIN EQUITY COMPANIES.

